04:20.467 --> 04:21.865
♪♪

04:21.867 --> 04:23.931
[ GEESE HONKING ]

04:23.933 --> 04:25.598
♪♪

04:25.600 --> 04:28.332
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

04:32.334 --> 04:34.398
YOUNG LADY.

04:34.400 --> 04:36.732
♪♪

04:36.734 --> 04:37.865
[ MUTTERING ]

04:37.867 --> 04:40.465
[ GROANS ]
YES.

04:42.334 --> 04:44.932
IT'S MY BIRTHDAY.

04:44.934 --> 04:47.332
I KNOW.

04:47.334 --> 04:49.398
[ SMOOCHES ] HAPPY BIRTHDAY.
THANK YOU.

04:49.400 --> 04:52.065
NOW, YOUR PARENTS ARE COMING
OVER AT 8:00 FOR BREAKFAST,

04:52.067 --> 04:55.932
AND THAT WILL GIVE US LESS
TIME WITH THE TEXT THAN USUAL.

04:55.934 --> 04:57.465
NO, NO, NO!
OKAY, BUT...

04:57.467 --> 04:59.165
[ GRUMBLING ]
MM!

05:06.334 --> 05:10.065
[ GROANS ] NO, NO.

05:10.067 --> 05:11.665
RISE!

05:11.667 --> 05:13.332
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

05:16.134 --> 05:17.532
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

05:17.534 --> 05:20.198
I HAVEN'T SEEN VERY
MUCH OF YOU LATELY.

05:20.200 --> 05:22.699
SEEMS LIKE SOME DAYS YOU
DON'T EVEN LEAVE THIS ROOM.

05:22.701 --> 05:24.365
WELL, I'M ON VACATION.

05:25.367 --> 05:27.565
YOUR BROTHER AND KERISSA
ARE ON THEIR WAY OVER,

05:27.567 --> 05:31.132
WITH WINKIE, FOR ZORA'S
LITTLE BIRTHDAY THINGY.

05:31.134 --> 05:32.899
IN THE MORNING?

05:32.901 --> 05:36.932
WELL, YOUR MOTHER HAS HER
ON 7:00 P.M. LOCKDOWN.

05:36.934 --> 05:39.932
THIS WAS THE ONLY TIME.

05:39.934 --> 05:41.465
WOW.

05:41.467 --> 05:43.198
WHEN IS SHE GONNA
GET IT TOGETHER?

05:43.200 --> 05:44.598
WHEN ARE<i> YOU?</i>

05:44.600 --> 05:46.798
WHEN ARE YOU MOVING OUT?

05:46.800 --> 05:49.198
IT'S HARD TO FIND A PLACE
WHEN EVERY SPARE PENNY

05:49.200 --> 05:51.798
IS IN THE SIGHTS OF THE
INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE.

05:51.800 --> 05:55.265
BUT IF MY PRESENCE IS THAT
TROUBLING TO YOU, I'LL JUST --

05:55.267 --> 05:56.465
DADDY.

05:59.067 --> 06:01.198
[ SIGHS ]

06:01.200 --> 06:02.932
IT'S JUST THAT I, UH...

06:02.934 --> 06:04.899
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

06:13.867 --> 06:15.231
I'LL MISS YOU.

06:15.233 --> 06:22.932
♪♪

06:22.934 --> 06:25.032
I'M GONNA MISS YOU, TOO.

06:25.034 --> 06:33.198
♪♪

06:33.200 --> 06:40.932
♪♪

06:40.934 --> 06:42.898
SEE IF YOU CAN MAKE IT DOWN.

06:42.900 --> 06:49.665
♪♪

06:49.667 --> 06:52.198
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

06:52.200 --> 06:59.565
♪♪

06:59.567 --> 07:03.132
[ SIGHS ]

07:03.134 --> 07:07.031
♪ HAPPY BIRTHDAY, DEAR ZORA ♪

07:07.033 --> 07:12.232
♪ HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO YOU ♪

07:12.234 --> 07:14.365
[ JAMES LAUGH ]

07:14.367 --> 07:16.231
-OH. MWAH.
-YEAH. MWAH.

07:16.233 --> 07:18.232
-HAPPY BIRTHDAY, SWEETHEART.
-THANKS.

07:18.234 --> 07:21.165
SUPER-SWEET, SUPER-SWEET.
-MM. HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

07:21.167 --> 07:23.765
Winkie: I GET TO EAT CAKE
FOR BREAKFAST?

07:23.767 --> 07:25.832
IF YOU PUT THE WORD
"COFFEE" IN FRONT OF IT.

07:25.834 --> 07:26.865
[ LAUGHTER ]

07:26.867 --> 07:28.799
BUT DON'T GET USED TO IT,
YOU HEAR?

07:28.801 --> 07:30.165
WE GOT A SURPRISE FOR YOU.

07:30.167 --> 07:31.798
[ GASPS ]

07:31.800 --> 07:33.398
IS IT MY PHONE?

07:33.400 --> 07:35.299
YOUR PHONE?
YEAH, THAT'S FUNNY.

07:37.167 --> 07:38.632
TICKETS TO SEE "HAMILTON"?

07:38.634 --> 07:39.765
-YES.
-OH!

07:39.767 --> 07:41.732
OKAY, SO, THERE ARE
ONLY TWO TICKETS,

07:41.734 --> 07:45.332
SO I THOUGHT WE COULD MAKE
A MOMMY-AND-DAUGHTER DATE.

07:45.334 --> 07:46.265
MM, YES, YES!
YES?

07:46.267 --> 07:48.598
[ LAUGHS ]

07:48.600 --> 07:49.865
WHEN'S THE PERFORMANCE?

07:49.867 --> 07:50.999
IT'S TOMORROW NIGHT.

07:51.001 --> 07:52.632
-OH.
-I'M EXCITED.

07:52.634 --> 07:54.865
WHAT A SHAME.

07:54.867 --> 07:56.598
WHY IS THAT A SHAME?

07:56.600 --> 07:58.932
WELL, ZORA'S ON PUNISHMENT.

07:58.934 --> 08:00.398
WELL...

08:00.400 --> 08:02.099
IT'S HER 18th BIRTHDAY.

08:02.101 --> 08:04.365
ACTIONS HAVE CONSEQUENCES.

08:04.367 --> 08:05.965
WELL, AREN'T
YOU GONNA SAY SOMETHING?

08:08.067 --> 08:11.865
MOM, YOU'RE BEING
A LITTLE TOUGH.

08:11.867 --> 08:15.598
A CLEAR UNDERSTANDING OF
HOW DEEPLY YOUR FAMILY CARES

08:15.600 --> 08:20.765
ABOUT YOUR SAFETY IS
A THING OF GREAT VALUE, JACOB.

08:20.767 --> 08:23.331
ONE WHOSE WORTH
MIGHT OUTLAST

08:23.333 --> 08:25.832
EVEN THAT OF SEEING
A BROADWAY MUSICAL.

08:27.100 --> 08:29.865
I AGREE.

08:29.867 --> 08:31.598
I CANNOT BELIEVE YOU.

08:31.600 --> 08:34.232
ARE YOU READY FOR SOME CAKE,
LITTLE MAN?

08:36.267 --> 08:38.132
[ LAUGHS ]

08:38.134 --> 08:41.198
SORRY, BABY.

08:41.200 --> 08:46.232
♪♪

08:46.234 --> 08:51.132
♪♪

08:51.134 --> 08:54.798
I'VE GOT ALL THE VENDORS
FROM LAST YEAR SAVING THE DATE,

08:54.800 --> 08:57.198
AND THE TEMPLETON
IS HOLDING THE BALLROOM

08:57.200 --> 08:58.465
WHILE WE FINALIZE
THE SCHEDULE.

08:58.467 --> 08:59.465
PERFECT.

08:59.467 --> 09:00.532
I'M SORRY.
THE TEMPLETON?

09:00.534 --> 09:02.465
WHAT'S THE PROBLEM NOW?

09:02.467 --> 09:04.665
AFTER WORKING WITH MAXINE
ALL THESE YEARS,

09:04.667 --> 09:05.865
BIGGER IS BETTER.

09:05.867 --> 09:08.798
I'M JUST WORRIED THE
TEMPLETON'S NOT GONNA DO IT.

09:08.800 --> 09:09.932
THAT WOMAN DRAWS A CROWD.

09:09.934 --> 09:11.631
DO YOU KNOW, I WAS
THINKING THE SAME THING.

09:11.633 --> 09:13.898
CAN'T WE JUST DO IT HERE?

09:13.900 --> 09:15.299
AT THE CHURCH?

09:16.934 --> 09:18.532
I LOVE THAT IDEA.

09:18.534 --> 09:21.665
THAT'S THE BISHOP'S
SILVER JUBILEE.

09:21.667 --> 09:23.199
SINCE WHEN?

09:23.201 --> 09:25.065
HE TOLD ME A FEW DAYS AGO.

09:25.067 --> 09:28.731
HE'S GONNA HAVE
A WHOLE CELEBRATION.

09:28.733 --> 09:30.532
WHILE WE'RE HAVING
"DAY WITH LADY MAE"

09:30.534 --> 09:32.732
AT THE TEMPLETON ACROSS TOWN?

09:32.734 --> 09:35.299
THAT'S NOT GONNA WORK.

09:35.301 --> 09:37.731
I JUST MEANT THAT
WE'D HAVE TO ASK HIM.

09:37.733 --> 09:39.065
I'M SURE HE'LL SAY YES.

09:39.067 --> 09:40.065
[ DOOR OPENS ]

09:41.667 --> 09:42.932
YOU WANTED TO SEE ME?

09:42.934 --> 09:45.399
YES.

09:45.401 --> 09:48.131
OH, KARINE,<i> I</i> WILL TALK
TO THE BISHOP ABOUT IT.

09:48.133 --> 09:50.332
I'M PERFECTLY WILLING
TO DO THAT.

09:50.334 --> 09:54.865
KARINE, LET ME CAUTION
YOU ABOUT OVERVALUING

09:54.867 --> 09:58.998
BISHOP'S OPINION IN THIS
TIME OF RAPID EVOLUTION.

09:59.000 --> 10:01.732
UNDERSTOOD.

10:01.734 --> 10:02.832
MY MISTAKE.

10:08.767 --> 10:09.965
WHAT DO YOU NEED?

10:09.967 --> 10:11.732
WELL, WE ARE COORDINATING

10:11.734 --> 10:15.332
WITH THE BOYS AND
GIRLS CLUB OF MEMPHIS

10:15.334 --> 10:18.332
SOME PROGRAMS FOR
"A DAY WITH LADY MAE,"

10:18.334 --> 10:21.199
AND THEIR C.E.O.
IS COMING OVER THIS MORNING.

10:21.201 --> 10:23.865
OF COURSE, I'M UP TO MY EARS
IN ALL OF THIS, AND I --

10:23.867 --> 10:25.565
WELL, I CAN'T MEET TODAY.

10:25.567 --> 10:27.165
BUT YOU'RE
THE DIRECTOR OF OUTREACH.

10:27.167 --> 10:28.898
I HAVE AN APPOINTMENT
AT THE COUNTY JAIL

10:28.900 --> 10:30.598
WITH CORALEE HUNTER.

10:30.600 --> 10:32.132
WAIT.

10:32.134 --> 10:34.465
WITH THE MURDERESS?

10:34.467 --> 10:36.532
THE<i> ACCUSED.</i>

10:36.534 --> 10:38.265
GRACE.

10:38.267 --> 10:41.465
I AM WORKING MY FINGERS
TO THE BONE

10:41.467 --> 10:43.998
TO TRY TO BREATHE
SOME NEW LIFE INTO THIS CHURCH

10:44.000 --> 10:46.598
THAT YOUR FATHER
NEARLY VANQUISHED HIMSELF

10:46.600 --> 10:48.598
WITH ALL
OF HIS NEGLIGENCE AND PRIDE.

10:48.600 --> 10:52.132
NOW, I WANT "A DAY WITH LADY
MAE" TO BE WHAT EVERYBODY

10:52.134 --> 10:54.132
IS TALKING ABOUT
OVER THE NEXT SIX WEEKS

10:54.134 --> 10:57.198
WHEN THEY HEAR
THE NAME "CALVARY"...

10:57.200 --> 10:59.398
AND NOT SOME TAWDRY WOMAN
WHO BLUDGEONED

10:59.400 --> 11:02.265
HER HUSBAND TO DEATH IN
HIS SLEEP WITH A HAMMER.

11:02.267 --> 11:06.065
MAMA, THE D.A.
IS TALKING DEATH PENALTY.

11:06.067 --> 11:07.965
A LIFE IS AT STAKE.

11:07.967 --> 11:09.898
AND DEFENDING THE RIGHTS
OF A VICTIM OF ABUSE --

11:09.900 --> 11:11.565
THAT'S AS GOOD
A CALLING CARD FOR A CHURCH

11:11.567 --> 11:13.598
AS SOME GLORIFIED PEP RALLY.

11:13.600 --> 11:15.799
PEP RALLY?
YEAH.

11:15.801 --> 11:19.198
IS THAT WHAT YOU AND YOUR
NEW BEST FRIEND MS. CROSS...

11:19.200 --> 11:21.332
[ CHUCKLES ]
...CALL THE FLAGSHIP EVENT

11:21.334 --> 11:22.899
FOR OUR CHURCH YEAR?

11:22.901 --> 11:25.032
MAMA, I HAVE MY REASONS
FOR WORKING WITH ROCHELLE

11:25.034 --> 11:26.598
ON THIS PROJECT.

11:26.600 --> 11:28.398
MM-HMM.

11:28.400 --> 11:32.465
SADISM AND SPITE,
BOTH AIMED DIRECTLY AT ME.

11:32.467 --> 11:33.998
GOSH.

11:34.000 --> 11:36.332
YOU UNDERSTAND ME PERFECTLY.

11:36.334 --> 11:39.865
AND YOU DON'T
UNDERSTAND ME AT ALL.

11:39.867 --> 11:46.699
♪♪

11:49.834 --> 11:53.298
♪♪

11:53.300 --> 11:57.265
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

11:57.267 --> 11:58.932
THOMPSON,
CASKET FUNERAL SERVICES.

11:58.934 --> 12:01.532
PERCY? JAMES.

12:01.534 --> 12:03.265
HOW MANY TIMES
DO I HAVE TO TELL YOU?

12:03.267 --> 12:05.265
WHEN YOU CALL,
USE YOUR CELLPHONE.

12:05.267 --> 12:07.932
YOU HAD ME TALKING ALL LIKE
WHITE FOLKS FOR NOTHING.

12:07.934 --> 12:09.399
[ CHUCKLES ]

12:09.401 --> 12:11.832
UH, LISTEN, I GOT TO
TALK TO YOU ABOUT --

12:13.134 --> 12:15.065
WELL, I'LL HAVE
TO CALL YOU BACK.

12:15.067 --> 12:17.565
YEAH, OKAY.

12:20.667 --> 12:22.398
MS. CROSS, I PRESUME.

12:22.400 --> 12:24.265
PERCY.
MM.

12:24.267 --> 12:25.598
AND HE SENDS HIS LOVE.

12:25.600 --> 12:28.365
AND, WELL...

12:28.367 --> 12:30.465
AND YOUR CONCERN TODAY IS?

12:30.467 --> 12:34.532
ARE YOU AWARE OF THE LATEST
INDIGNITIES OUR DAUGHTER

12:34.534 --> 12:36.665
HAS DRAGGED LIKE A RAT
TO OUR DOORSTEP?

12:36.667 --> 12:40.199
WHICH DAUGHTER,
AND WHICH INDIGNITY?

12:40.201 --> 12:41.498
GRACE...

12:41.500 --> 12:44.532
AND THIS MURDERESS
THAT SHE'S DECIDED TO SPONSOR

12:44.534 --> 12:45.932
LIKE SOME CHILD
FROM AFRICA.

12:45.934 --> 12:47.265
AND WITH CHURCH MONEY.

12:47.267 --> 12:48.765
I HEARD.

12:48.767 --> 12:51.331
DON'T YOU THINK IT'S BAD
ENOUGH THAT EVERYONE KNOWS

12:51.333 --> 12:54.131
ABOUT YOUR TROUBLES
WITH THE TAX MAN?

12:54.133 --> 12:56.899
I MEAN, DO YOU THINK
THIS IS GOOD P.R. RIGHT NOW?

12:56.901 --> 13:00.765
MAE...

13:00.767 --> 13:01.965
HAVE A SEAT, PLEASE.

13:01.967 --> 13:03.699
WHAT?
PLEASE.

13:03.701 --> 13:05.532
[ SIGHS ]

13:12.200 --> 13:18.132
NOW, THE LORD HAS PROVIDED US
A WAY TO PAY WHAT WE OWE

13:18.134 --> 13:19.431
TO THE TAX MAN.

13:19.433 --> 13:22.065
AT LEAST TO GET STARTED,
ANYWAY.

13:24.034 --> 13:26.198
I'M LISTENING.

13:26.200 --> 13:28.198
BUT, JAMES, THIS IS<i> YOU.</i>

13:28.200 --> 13:29.532
MAE...
IT'S NOT<i> ME.</i>

13:29.534 --> 13:31.765
YOUR NAME
WAS ON THOSE RETURNS.

13:31.767 --> 13:33.965
WHATEVER YOU SAY, YOU KNEW.

13:33.967 --> 13:36.298
WELL, HOW DO YOU
PROPOSE TO PAY FOR IT?

13:36.300 --> 13:38.199
[ SIGHS ]

13:41.567 --> 13:46.532
BY MAKING A SUBSTANTIAL-
BUT-SHORT-TERM INVESTMENT

13:46.534 --> 13:48.332
IN CRYPTOCURRENCY.

13:48.334 --> 13:51.265
OH.

13:51.267 --> 13:54.198
THIS IS
ROCHELLE'S GENIUS AT WORK.

13:54.200 --> 13:57.865
MS. CROSS ASSURES ME --

13:57.867 --> 14:01.198
THAT STRUMPET WALTZED
INTO OUR CHURCH, JAMES,

14:01.200 --> 14:04.665
WITH A BAD REPUTATION
AND EARNED IT ALL OVER AGAIN.

14:04.667 --> 14:05.798
NOW, ISN'T IT ENOUGH

14:05.800 --> 14:09.665
THAT SHE HAS BROKEN
OUR FAMILY IN HALF?

14:09.667 --> 14:11.665
DO YOU HAVE TO LET HER
TAKE ALL OF OUR MONEY, TOO?

14:11.667 --> 14:13.132
SHE'S TRYING TO HELP US BOTH.

14:13.134 --> 14:15.798
OH, YOU KNOW WHAT?

14:15.800 --> 14:17.265
THAT PREACHER WAS RIGHT.

14:17.267 --> 14:18.865
OH, WHAT PREACHER?

14:18.867 --> 14:21.665
THE ONE
WHO WROTE ECCLESIASTES.

14:21.667 --> 14:23.798
"BETTER TO BE
A POOR, WISE YOUTH

14:23.800 --> 14:25.732
THAN AN OLD, FOOLISH KING

14:25.734 --> 14:28.765
WHO CAN
NO LONGER HEED ADVICE."

14:30.934 --> 14:33.932
YOUR BLINDNESS
IN REGARDS TO THIS WOMAN

14:33.934 --> 14:36.332
IS TRULY ASTONISHING.

14:36.334 --> 14:38.865
MAE...

14:38.867 --> 14:41.132
I WILL SPEAK TO GRACE
AND CALL HER OFF

14:41.134 --> 14:43.398
IF YOU'LL MEET ME
HALFWAY IN THIS.

14:43.400 --> 14:47.265
NOW, I'VE ALREADY PUT MOST OF
MY PERSONAL ACCOUNT INTO IT.

14:47.267 --> 14:49.065
WHAT...

14:49.067 --> 14:52.132
WHAT WE HAVE
IN OUR SHARED ACCOUNT

14:52.134 --> 14:54.265
WILL GET US
WHERE WE NEED TO GO.

14:54.267 --> 14:57.432
WHERE<i> YOU</i> NEED TO GO.

14:59.400 --> 15:04.665
NOT IN A BILLION YEARS.

15:04.667 --> 15:08.265
YOU MADE ALL THESE BEDS.

15:08.267 --> 15:09.465
YOU LIE IN THEM.

15:09.467 --> 15:10.932
[ SIGHS ]

15:10.934 --> 15:17.631
♪♪

15:17.633 --> 15:24.465
♪♪

15:24.467 --> 15:31.032
♪♪

15:31.034 --> 15:32.432
HEY.

15:32.434 --> 15:34.032
[ WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
ON P.A. ]

15:34.034 --> 15:35.498
THANK YOU.

15:35.500 --> 15:39.532
♪♪

15:39.534 --> 15:41.065
THAT'S IT?
YES.

15:41.067 --> 15:42.099
JUST THIRD
DOWN THE HALLWAY.

15:42.101 --> 15:43.432
THANK YOU.

15:43.434 --> 15:45.965
PASTOR GREENLEAF.

15:45.967 --> 15:47.698
WESTON PRICE.

15:47.700 --> 15:50.865
THE D.A. WHO ELECTED NOT
TO TRY YOU FOR MANSLAUGHTER.

15:50.867 --> 15:53.065
RIGHT.

15:53.067 --> 15:56.065
THANK YOU.

15:56.067 --> 15:57.832
WHAT BRINGS YOU DOWN HERE?

15:57.834 --> 15:59.565
CORALEE HUNTER.

15:59.567 --> 16:00.865
SHE GOES TO CALVARY?

16:00.867 --> 16:02.132
NO.

16:02.134 --> 16:03.665
WE JUST RECENTLY STARTED
A LEGAL DEFENSE FUND

16:03.667 --> 16:05.065
FOR VICTIMS LIKE HER.

16:05.067 --> 16:08.465
CORALEE HUNTER
IS NO VICTIM.

16:08.467 --> 16:11.865
SHE MURDERED HER HUSBAND
IN HIS SLEEP

16:11.867 --> 16:14.865
WITH A HAMMER HE HAD
USED JUST HOURS EARLIER

16:14.867 --> 16:17.398
TO HANG
A PICTURE OF HIS FAMILY.

16:17.400 --> 16:18.932
THEN I ASSUME
YOU KNOW WHAT HE ALSO DID

16:18.934 --> 16:20.865
WITH THAT HAMMER
IN THE PAST.

16:20.867 --> 16:24.798
THERE ISN'T EVEN A SHRED
OF ADMISSIBLE EVIDENCE

16:24.800 --> 16:26.332
THAT HE EVER ABUSED HER.

16:26.334 --> 16:28.932
WELL, I'M CONTENT TO
LET A JUDGE DECIDE

16:28.934 --> 16:31.132
WHAT'S ADMISSIBLE
AND INADMISSIBLE.

16:31.134 --> 16:32.132
EXCUSE ME.

16:32.134 --> 16:33.965
GRACE.

16:33.967 --> 16:35.932
YOU KNOW, YOU'RE
STARTING TO SOUND

16:35.934 --> 16:38.598
LIKE YOU'RE THE ONE WITHOUT
A CASE HERE, COUNSELOR.

16:38.600 --> 16:43.065
SOMETIMES I HAND
A CASE OFF TO ANOTHER D.A.

16:43.067 --> 16:47.398
BECAUSE
I CAN'T BE OBJECTIVE.

16:47.400 --> 16:50.665
THAT POND YOU'RE
ABOUT TO STEP INTO,

16:50.667 --> 16:53.465
IT MIGHT BE A LOT
DEEPER THAN YOU THINK.

16:53.467 --> 17:03.465
♪♪

17:03.467 --> 17:04.598
<i> SORRY, PHOEBE.</i>
<i> I FORGOT MY KEY.</i>

17:04.600 --> 17:05.732
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

17:05.734 --> 17:06.998
<i> WHENEVER THERE'S A RING</i>
<i> AT THE DOOR,</i>

17:07.000 --> 17:08.199
<i> I DON'T LIKE TO ANSWER IT</i>

17:08.201 --> 17:09.399
<i> IN CASE IT'S</i>
<i> A POLICEMAN STANDING THERE</i>

17:09.401 --> 17:10.931
<i> WITH ANOTHER SUMMONS.</i>
[ RINGING CONTINUES ]

17:10.933 --> 17:12.665
<i> THERE'LL BE A POLICEMAN</i>
<i> AT THE DOOR, ALL RIGHT.</i>

17:12.667 --> 17:14.532
HELLO?

17:14.534 --> 17:16.398
YEAH, CHARITY,
THIS IS PERCY LEE.

17:16.400 --> 17:18.332
PERCY, DADDY'S FRIEND?

17:18.334 --> 17:21.065
Yeah.
So, how are you, angel?

17:21.067 --> 17:24.665
I'M -- I'M FINE, I GUESS.

17:24.667 --> 17:25.865
WHY ARE YOU CALLING ME?

17:25.867 --> 17:27.932
I GOT THIS MEMORIAL
SERVICE HERE TONIGHT,

17:27.934 --> 17:29.865
AND THE SINGER JUST CALLED
AND SAYS SHE HAS THE FLU

17:29.867 --> 17:31.532
THAT EVERYBODY'S GOT.

17:31.534 --> 17:33.665
SO I THOUGHT
MAYBE YOU WOULD STEP IN

17:33.667 --> 17:36.465
AND OFFER
SOME MUSICAL COMFORT.

17:36.467 --> 17:39.198
Hope it's all right
to ask.

17:39.200 --> 17:41.932
YEAH. UM, BUT...

17:41.934 --> 17:43.265
PERCY, I DON'T KNOW.

17:43.267 --> 17:45.132
I'M...

17:45.134 --> 17:48.065
I'M NOT SURE I CAN BE
OF COMFORT RIGHT NOW.

17:48.067 --> 17:51.665
THIS FAMILY JUST LOST
THEIR GREAT-GREAT-GRANDMOTHER,

17:51.667 --> 17:53.598
AND SHE'S THE HEART
AND SOUL OF THE FAMILY,

17:53.600 --> 17:56.132
AND THEY'RE ALL TORE UP,
AND ALL I GOT

17:56.134 --> 17:58.798
IS SOME PRERECORDED
ORGAN MUSIC AND SPOTIFY.

17:58.800 --> 18:00.265
[ CHUCKLES ]

18:00.267 --> 18:01.932
So, just one or two songs?

18:01.934 --> 18:05.599
OR AM I GONNA HAVE TO
CALL THAT DADDY OF YOURS

18:05.601 --> 18:09.265
and get him to come up there
and harass you to do all this?

18:09.267 --> 18:11.198
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

18:11.200 --> 18:16.598
♪♪

18:16.600 --> 18:18.665
YOUR MOTHER
IS BEING TOO STRICT.

18:18.667 --> 18:22.598
MY MOTHER IS BEING FIRM.
THAT'S THE POINT.

18:22.600 --> 18:24.132
IF YOU WEREN'T BEING
SO PRIDEFUL ABOUT THIS,

18:24.134 --> 18:26.065
YOU'D SEE THE WISDOM
IN IT.

18:26.067 --> 18:27.932
ISN'T BEING STRICT
YOUR WHOLE BRAND?

18:27.934 --> 18:30.132
ZORA IS 18.

18:30.134 --> 18:32.265
IF SHE DECIDES TO LEAVE,
THERE'S NOTHING ME, YOU,

18:32.267 --> 18:35.099
OR YOUR ALL-SEEING, ALL-KNOWING
MOTHER CAN DO ABOUT IT.

18:35.101 --> 18:37.198
MY MOTHER KNOWS
WHAT SHE'S DOING.

18:37.200 --> 18:38.865
IF YOUR MOTHER KNEW
WHAT SHE WAS DOING,

18:38.867 --> 18:41.165
IT WOULDN'T HAVE TAKEN ME
NEARLY 20 YEARS TO GET YOU

18:41.167 --> 18:42.932
TO STRAIGHTEN UP
AND FLY RIGHT.

18:44.767 --> 18:47.565
I'M GONNA GO TALK TO HER.

18:47.567 --> 18:48.865
GO AHEAD.

18:48.867 --> 18:50.665
I WASN'T ASKING
FOR PERMISSION!

18:50.667 --> 18:51.732
[ DOOR OPENS ]
SORRY.

18:51.734 --> 18:53.132
MY MISTAKE.

18:53.134 --> 18:54.132
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

18:54.134 --> 18:55.465
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

18:55.467 --> 18:57.665
[ MAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
ON P.A. ]

18:57.667 --> 18:59.465
♪♪

18:59.467 --> 19:01.932
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

19:01.934 --> 19:04.165
♪♪

19:04.167 --> 19:06.365
[ POUNDING ON DOOR ]

19:06.367 --> 19:11.798
♪♪

19:11.800 --> 19:17.132
♪♪

19:17.134 --> 19:22.498
♪♪

19:22.500 --> 19:24.465
[ GRUNTS ]
[ SCREAMS ]

19:24.467 --> 19:26.699
[ DOOR OPENS ]

19:35.500 --> 19:37.232
THANK YOU.

19:40.034 --> 19:42.199
HI, CORALEE.

19:42.201 --> 19:44.998
YOU DON'T LOOK SO GOOD.

19:45.000 --> 19:47.265
I'M FINE.
[ CHUCKLES ]

19:47.267 --> 19:49.198
THIS [CLEARS THROAT]

19:49.200 --> 19:51.732
THIS ROOM JUST GOT A LITTLE
SMALL THERE FOR A MINUTE.

19:54.734 --> 19:56.865
DO YOU KNOW WHY I'M HERE?

19:56.867 --> 19:58.532
YOU'RE FROM SOME CHURCH.

19:58.534 --> 20:00.732
YEAH.
MM.

20:00.734 --> 20:02.998
WE HAVE A FUND THAT
PROVIDES LEGAL AID

20:03.000 --> 20:07.665
TO PEOPLE
WITH CASES LIKE YOURS.

20:07.667 --> 20:09.465
I DON'T BELIEVE IN GOD.

20:09.467 --> 20:11.598
THAT'S WHY YOU'RE HERE --
TO SAVE MY SOUL.

20:11.600 --> 20:14.065
IT'S NOT.

20:14.067 --> 20:15.965
I'M HERE TO HELP, CORALEE.

20:17.867 --> 20:19.932
'CAUSE I WAS VERY...

20:21.934 --> 20:25.198
I WAS ONCE VERY CLOSE TO
SITTING EXACTLY WHERE YOU ARE.

20:25.200 --> 20:26.565
HOW?

20:26.567 --> 20:27.799
[ SIGHS ]

20:27.801 --> 20:29.065
LET'S TALK ABOUT YOU.

20:29.067 --> 20:35.565
♪♪

20:39.067 --> 20:41.599
[ WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
ON P.A. ]

20:44.534 --> 20:46.132
HE HAD ME PINNED DOWN.

20:46.134 --> 20:48.198
HE WAS CHOKING ME.

20:48.200 --> 20:49.665
IF HE HADN'T BEEN
BLIND DRUNK,

20:49.667 --> 20:51.431
I'D PROBABLY BE
THE ONE DEAD TODAY.

20:51.433 --> 20:53.432
♪♪

20:53.434 --> 20:55.065
[ GRUNTS ]

20:55.067 --> 20:57.598
AND THAT'S WHEN YOU DECIDED.

20:57.600 --> 20:59.599
I NEVER DECIDED ANYTHING.

21:05.334 --> 21:07.332
I DON'T EVEN
REMEMBER DOING IT.

21:11.867 --> 21:13.599
UNDERSTOOD.

21:17.800 --> 21:20.198
I'M GLAD IT HAPPENED,
THOUGH.

21:20.200 --> 21:22.265
FOR THE KIDS' SAKE
IF NOTHING ELSE.

21:22.267 --> 21:24.665
HE ABUSED THE KIDS, TOO,
HUH?

21:24.667 --> 21:27.565
NO, HE JUST THREATENED TO
ALL THE TIME

21:27.567 --> 21:28.965
TO GET ME TO...

21:33.134 --> 21:36.598
YOU KNOW --
WHATEVER HE WANTED TO DO.

21:36.600 --> 21:39.532
Guard: TIME'S UP.

21:43.534 --> 21:45.265
I'M GONNA SEE YOU SOON.

21:45.267 --> 21:47.532
WILL YOU REALLY?

21:47.534 --> 21:49.265
YEAH.

21:49.267 --> 21:53.265
♪♪

